   <pb facs="34"/>
   <head>M.<seg rend="sup">r.</seg> M. D. TO THE AVTHOR.</head>
   <lg>
      <l>SVch was old <hi>Orpheus</hi> cunning,</l>
      <l>That sencelesse things drew neere him,</l>
      <l>And heards of beasts to heare him,</l>
      <l>The stock, the stone, the Oxe, the Asse came running.</l>
      <l>
         <hi>MORLEY!</hi> but this enchaunting</l>
      <l>To thee, to be the Musick God is wanting.</l>
      <l>And yet thou needst not feare him;</l>
      <l>Draw thou the Shepherds still and Bonny-lasses,</l>
      <l>And enuie him not stocks, stones, Oxen, Asses.</l>
   </lg>
</div>
